text: Wallace Leschinsky (May 12, 1920 - September 20, 1976)Wisconsin Death Index 1957-1999 was an American politician and businessman. Born in Beloit, Wisconsin, Leschinsky served in the United States Army during World War II. He went to Rockford Business College in Rockford, Illinois and was a salesman and restaurant owner. In 1955, Leschinsky served in the Wisconsin State Assembly and was a Republican. He died in Beloit, Wisconsin.'Wisconsin Blue Book 1958,' Biographical Sketch of Wallace Leschinsky, pg. 62 ==Notes== Category:1920 births Category:1976 deaths Category:Politicians from Beloit, Wisconsin Category:Military personnel from Wisconsin Category:Businesspeople from Wisconsin Category:Wisconsin Republicans Category:Members of the Wisconsin State Assembly Category:American military personnel of World War II Category:20th-century American businesspeople Category:20th-century American politicians
